Import modules

Import ==> keyword
Turtle ==> module names

How to make class

Import turtle
Tim = turtle.Turtle() ==> here, we first import module and then to create class we use turtle.Turtle() module.class  but Instead to do this we can do this

From turtle import Turtle ==> keyword module keyword thing in module
Tim = Turtle()
Tom = Turtle()

Another method is *
We can use it to import all the things from module but there is an disadvantages too, it make confusing from where the classes or methods are comming from for example,
From random import *
Choice([1,2,3])
Now we don’t from where choice is comming from


Aliasing Method
import turtle as t ==> keyword module keyword alias name
Tim = t.Turle()

https://pypi.org/



